    "long_instructions": "### Loops & Cues\r\n\r\n**Define:** Great performers know how to handle surprises, like a DJ adjusting a mix or a band improvising during a live show. In this challenge, you'll use the `random` block to prepare for unexpected changes and practice reacting in real-time. We'll learn more about this block in the next lesson - for now: follow the steps below!\r\n\r\n**Prepare:**\r\n- There are 3 tracks inside the `play random` block - update them to be three different vocal tracks from Fireworks by Katy Perry [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=id:play_workspace)\r\n- Add your own backing beat and bass track to the vocals [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=id:repeat_workspace)\r\n- Create 3 triggers that start on the \"next beat\" - one for each of the vocal tracks. Inside each trigger, add a small loop and a few tracks to play that go with each track\r\n\r\n**Try:** Perform your song! As you play, one of the vocal tracks will be randomly chosen to play. React in real-time to each vocal track, adjusting your timing as needed.\r\n\r\n**Reflect:** Play through the song a few times. Were you able to respond in time? How did your choices help you stay flexible? In order to complete this level, your remix must include:\r\n\r\n- 3 different vocal tracks from *Fireworks* inside a `play random` block\r\n- 1 backing beat and 1 bass track\r\n- 3 triggers that each start on the \"next beat,\" with loops and supporting tracks inside\r\n- A live performance where you react in real time to the randomly chosen vocal",
    "exemplar_settings": {
      "playerEnabled": false,
      "validationEnabled": false
    },
